On the main setup panel you can enable spool normalization.

It is also possible to select (and sort) a subset of pages of the input spool file by means of a specific xml data file.

After enabling this mode, you will need to fully configure it in order for the feature to work correctly.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Name**

**Description**

**Enable processing of existing spool files**

Allows to enable the following setting spool.

**Datasection for page selection**

Selects the datasection used as a page selector. A page will be emitted in the output spool for ea datasection must contain the attributes that identify source, target files and other options (followi

**Input format**

Allows to select the type of input file format supported: MO:DCA, Line Mode / Mixed Mode.

**Input spool file name**

File name of the source file

**Page position in the input file**

Indicates the position of the page inside the source file.

**Page is fill**

Allows you to select an attribute that indicates that the page is empty (when such attribute is present on the page, it must be printed but devoid of content).

**Page has "Pagetag1"**

Indicates that the page is associated to the *Pagetag1 *attribute. (This will have no effect on the display of the output document. It will only be used by Document Composition to identify pages that use it, e.g. when creating indexes).

**Page has "Pagetag2"**

Indicates that the page is associated to the *Pagetag2 *attribute.

**Page has "Pagetag3"**

Indicates that the page is associated to the *Pagetag3 *attribute.

**Page has "Pagetag4"**

Indicates that the page is associated to the *Pagetag4 *attribute.

**Page rotation**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Allows you to set up the rotation of the pages by selecting one of the available options:

- **None: **No rotation is applied (default).

- **90**: 90-degree clockwise rotation applied to all pages.

- **180**: 180-degree clockwise rotation applied to all pages.

- **270**: 270-degree clockwise rotation applied to all pages.

- **Auto**: The best rotation is automatically applied to each individual page based on the angle of the text. The rotation is also applied to white pages, which follow the previous page format (vertical/ horizontal)

**Enable Generation of documents fetching pages from data**

**section:**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Allows you to enable the generation of documents using pages inserted in the input file.

> Warning

The data section of the input file where the pages will be found must be configured. The pages from the input file completely replace the pages configured in the designer.

## Advanced settings
In this area of the general panel the user can view the information in XML, of input file previously selected in the drop-down menu **Input Format**. To view you can switch between the tabs: **MO:DCA **or **Line Mode / Mixed Mode**.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Additional Configurations
This section is dedicated to additional configurations of the spool normalizer module:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Tab**

**Description**

**FORMDEF processing settings**

Used to configure the processing settings of the FORMDEF element of AFP files. It accepts a configuration in XML Format.

**Embedded normalizer settings**

XML configuration of the embedded spool normalizer.

**PDF Settings**

Contains specific settings for the processing of PDF files. The user can view and edit the settings in XML format.
